title: "Final Draft Board | Podcast"
description: "We've reviewed boards from all our guests but today we run through Adam's evaluation approach, board, and specific players of interest in each pick range for the Utah Jazz."
author: "Adam Bushman"
date: "2023-06-19"
categories: [2023-24, draft, preview]
image: "thumbnail.png"
draft: false
---

::: {.cell}

:::



## Intro

Welcome to Jabber Jazz | Fan-driven, Ad-free content on Utah Jazz basketball

Adam Bushman [Twitter | @adam_bushman](https://www.twitter.com/adam_bushman)

Today:

*   Run through final big board
    -   Chat risers/fallers
    -   Orient to industry expectation
*   Execute final draft simulation


Like what we're doing? Consider...

*   Subscribing
*   Following
*   Leaving a review or comment
*   Snagging some merch

Let's Jabber Jazz!


## Approach

*   Measureables (height, weight, etc.)
*   Positions (offense, defense)
*   Impression of how they carry themselves
*   Physical traits
*   Offense, defense traits
*   Comparisons to NBA forerunners 
*   Disclaimer on order and tiers
    -   No confidence short term (first half of rookie deal) any player is better/worse than another
    -   Tiers demonstrate confidence in long term (4-6 years) that the avg player in T1 > T2
    -   Order within the tier is based on personal preference


::: {.cell}

:::

